<i>try to recruit
staff for subsequent</i>

27:40.836 --> 27:42.751
<i>proceedings after the.</i>

27:42.792 --> 27:45.000
<i>International Military
Trial was finished.</i>

27:46.542 --> 27:48.709
<i>And he said there's somebody</i>

27:48.710 --> 27:51.209
<i>else wants to talk to
you and that was then</i>

27:51.210 --> 27:53.667
<i>colonel Telford Taylor.</i>

27:54.792 --> 27:56.396
<i>Telford Taylor had been</i>

27:56.397 --> 27:58.000
<i>assigned by president Truman</i>

27:58.042 --> 28:00.167
<i>to carry on the work of Jackson</i>

28:00.209 --> 28:01.834
<i>by being the chief of counsel</i>

28:01.835 --> 28:03.459
<i>for the 12 subsequent trials</i>

28:03.500 --> 28:04.959
<i>were being planned.</i>

28:05.000 --> 28:08.792
<i>"So he said" I'm
considering you know</i>

28:08.834 --> 28:10.417
<i>you going back with me," he said</i>

28:10.459 --> 28:12.480
<i>"but I have checked your army"</i>

28:12.481 --> 28:14.500
<i>record and your background</i>

28:14.542 --> 28:16.438
<i>and I understand that you're</i>

28:16.439 --> 28:18.334
<i>"occasionally insubordinate'"</i>

28:18.375 --> 28:20.125
and I said "That's not
correct, sir."

28:20.167 --> 28:22.292
I'm usually insubordinate.

28:22.334 --> 28:24.105
I do not obey any orders that

28:24.106 --> 28:26.980
I know are stupid or
illegal, but I've been

28:26.981 --> 28:28.042
"checking up on you too,"

28:28.083 --> 28:29.709
and I had in the interim,

28:29.751 --> 28:31.727
- "and I don't think you'll.
- Give me that kind of order."

28:31.751 --> 28:33.584
He was also a Harvard graduate,

28:33.626 --> 28:35.542
and he'd checked my record.

28:35.584 --> 28:36.709
So he smiled and he said.

28:36.710 --> 28:37.834
"You'll go with me."

28:42.918 --> 28:45.751
<i>These were to be 12
additional trials</i>

28:45.792 --> 28:47.813
<i>because it was recognized</i>

28:47.814 --> 28:49.834
<i>by just taking a snapshot</i>

28:49.876 --> 28:52.001
<i>of the International Military.</i>

28:52.002 --> 28:54.938
<i>Tribunal top Nazi
leaders, you still didn't</i>

28:54.939 --> 28:56.959
<i>quite understand how
it would be possible</i>

28:57.000 --> 28:59.792
<i>for a civilized
country like Germany</i>

28:59.834 --> 29:01.792
<i>to engage in the
type of atrocities</i>

29:01.834 --> 29:03.751
<i>for which they were responsible.</i>

29:03.792 --> 29:04.792
And the idea of these

29:04.793 --> 29:05.793
subsequent proceedings,

29:05.834 --> 29:07.584
as they were called, was to

29:07.585 --> 29:09.334
put the doctors on trial,

29:09.375 --> 29:11.042
<i>a sampling who performed</i>

29:11.043 --> 29:12.709
<i>medical experiments</i>

29:12.751 --> 29:14.834
<i>on concentration camp inmates.</i>

29:14.876 --> 29:16.001
<i>The lawyers and judges</i>

29:16.002 --> 29:17.125
<i>who perverted the law</i>

29:17.167 --> 29:18.813
<i>which was the framework on</i>

29:18.814 --> 29:20.459
<i>which they built the film.</i>

29:20.500 --> 29:22.125
Judgment at Nuremberg.

29:22.167 --> 29:26.209
You had the industrialists
like IG Farben

29:26.250 --> 29:29.042
<i>who provided the money
to build Auschwitz,</i>

29:29.083 --> 29:30.813
<i>and who were working people</i>

29:30.814 --> 29:32.542
<i>to death for their own profit</i>

29:32.584 --> 29:33.792
<i>in their own companies.</i>

29:33.834 --> 29:36.250
<i>Give them a chance
to state their case.</i>

29:36.292 --> 29:37.959
<i>The foreign ministry people,</i>

29:37.960 --> 29:39.626
<i>and then the SS squads</i>

29:39.667 --> 29:40.772
<i>who were the real, the</i>

29:40.773 --> 29:41.876
<i>murderers on the scene.</i>

29:41.918 --> 29:43.959
<i>So the idea was
to take a sampling</i>

29:44.000 --> 29:45.730
for these 12 different

29:45.731 --> 29:47.459
categories and project that

29:47.500 --> 29:49.918
and through the form
of these 12 trials

29:49.959 --> 29:51.709
to give a comprehensive picture,

29:51.751 --> 29:53.417
<i>and Telford Taylor was to be</i>

29:53.418 --> 29:55.083
<i>chief of counsel for those 12.</i>

29:57.042 --> 29:59.417
<i>I can imagine no two
more different people</i>

29:59.459 --> 30:01.792
<i>than Telford Taylor and Ben.</i>

30:01.834 --> 30:04.459
Telford, this very tall,

30:04.460 --> 30:07.083
elegant, WASPy gentlemen

30:08.167 --> 30:10.334
<i>who could not have been</i>

30:10.335 --> 30:12.500
<i>more polite and thoughtful,</i>

30:12.542 --> 30:13.647
you never got a quick

30:13.648 --> 30:14.751
answer out of Telford.

30:14.792 --> 30:17.584
It was always let
me think about that.

30:17.626 --> 30:20.001
<i>And then this kind of dynamo</i>

30:20.002 --> 30:22.375
<i>of a tiny little Jewish guy</i>

30:23.918 --> 30:25.855
<i>with none of the kind</i>

30:25.856 --> 30:27.792
<i>of elegance of Telford.</i>

30:27.834 --> 30:29.101
He had the same
elegance of mind,

30:29.125 --> 30:32.626
<i>but not elegance of
physical appearance.</i>

30:32.667 --> 30:35.083
<i>I can easily see the attraction.</i>

30:36.250 --> 30:39.792
<i>He was brilliant,
insightful, determined.</i>

30:39.834 --> 30:41.313
<i>He had all the qualities</i>

30:41.314 --> 30:42.792
<i>that one would look for</i>

30:42.834 --> 30:44.250
<i>if one were Telford Taylor.</i>

30:48.792 --> 30:51.709
<i>By the time we got
there to that stage,</i>

30:51.751 --> 30:53.314
he had already picked lawyers

30:53.315 --> 30:54.876
for most of his trials,

30:54.918 --> 30:56.397
and he said "Ben look, you have"

30:56.398 --> 30:57.876
the experience in the field

30:57.918 --> 30:59.250
of going into the camps,

30:59.292 --> 31:02.834
collecting evidence
for the army trials.

31:02.876 --> 31:05.167
We have a number of suspects,

31:05.209 --> 31:06.605
but if you have a suspect and

31:06.606 --> 31:08.000
no evidence you have nothing.

31:08.042 --> 31:11.250
"Your job is to go
find the evidence."

31:11.292 --> 31:13.417
So I took a staff
of about 50 people

31:13.459 --> 31:16.375
and went to Berlin,
set up the organization

31:16.417 --> 31:17.751
<i>to start searching
in the archives</i>

31:17.792 --> 31:19.626
<i>of the Foreign Ministry,</i>

31:19.667 --> 31:21.896
<i>the SS, the Gestapo, the</i>

31:21.897 --> 31:24.125
<i>army, and the industrialists</i>

31:24.167 --> 31:27.709
<i>to see what evidence
we had that they had</i>

31:27.710 --> 31:29.167
<i>committed war crimes.</i>

31:29.209 --> 31:31.438
It was in that capacity that

31:31.439 --> 31:33.667
one of my staff members,

31:33.709 --> 31:35.188
a boy from Switzerland came

31:35.189 --> 31:36.667
and he said look what I found

31:36.709 --> 31:38.959
in the offices of
the Foreign Ministry,

31:39.000 --> 31:41.375
and it was a complete dossier,

31:41.417 --> 31:44.292
<i>the daily reports
coming in from the front</i>

31:44.334 --> 31:45.813
<i>saying how many Jews</i>

31:45.814 --> 31:47.292
<i>these units had murdered.</i>

31:47.334 --> 31:50.083
<i>Now these units were
called Einsatzgruppe,</i>

31:50.125 --> 31:52.292
<i>and it was
deliberately disguised</i>

31:52.334 --> 31:55.584
<i>so you couldn't tell from</i>

31:55.585 --> 31:58.334
<i>the name what it
was, because their</i>

31:58.335 --> 32:01.626
<i>assignment was to go
in</i> behind the German

31:58.375 --> 32:01.626
lines and then murder,

32:01.667 --> 32:03.167
they never used the word murder,

32:03.209 --> 32:05.292
they said eliminate,
exterminate,

32:05.334 --> 32:06.792
<i>every single Jewish man, woman,</i>

32:06.793 --> 32:08.250
<i>and child they could lay</i>

32:08.292 --> 32:10.292
their hands on and do the same

32:10.293 --> 32:12.188
thing for the Gypsies
and do the same thing

32:12.189 --> 32:14.042
for any suspected

32:14.083 --> 32:15.876
possible enemies of the Reich.

32:15.918 --> 32:17.876
<i>That was their job.</i>

32:17.918 --> 32:19.335
<i>They had these daily</i>

32:19.336 --> 32:20.751
<i>reports sent back to Berlin</i>

32:20.792 --> 32:22.584
<i>where they were consolidated</i>

32:22.585 --> 32:24.375
<i>and put together in a folder</i>

32:24.417 --> 32:25.668
and then each of those

32:25.669 --> 32:26.918
reports was sent down

32:26.959 --> 32:28.792
and I had the distribution list,

32:28.834 --> 32:30.501
to 99 different branches

32:30.502 --> 32:32.167
of the German government.

32:32.209 --> 32:33.834
To people like the army who said

32:33.876 --> 32:35.250
I never heard
anything about that

32:35.292 --> 32:37.375
down in my area and so on.

32:37.417 --> 32:38.876
That was baloney, they are

32:38.877 --> 32:40.334
under my distribution list

32:40.375 --> 32:41.938
so I took an adding machine

32:41.939 --> 32:43.500
and began to add them up

32:43.542 --> 32:45.230
and when I reached a

32:45.231 --> 32:46.918
million people murdered,

32:46.959 --> 32:48.417
I said that's enough.

32:48.459 --> 32:50.105
I took a sampling, took

32:50.106 --> 32:52.855
the next plane from
Berlin where I had the

32:52.856 --> 32:53.918
headquarters for that,

32:53.959 --> 32:55.167
went down to Nuremberg

32:55.168 --> 32:56.375
and I said "General,"

32:56.417 --> 32:58.375
by that time he
had been promoted,

32:58.417 --> 33:00.959
"we got to put on a new trial."

33:04.626 --> 33:08.459
<i>The Einsatzgruppe
were task forces</i>

33:08.500 --> 33:10.125
<i>moving behind the front lines</i>

33:10.167 --> 33:13.792
<i>and their only
purpose was to kill.</i>

33:13.834 --> 33:17.751
<i>Jews, minorities,
and opposition.</i>

33:17.792 --> 33:21.709
So they were really
like killing squads.

33:21.751 --> 33:25.918
These were the forces
that rode around

33:25.959 --> 33:29.584
and machine gunned

33:29.626 --> 33:34.667
<i>whole villages and communities</i>

33:34.709 --> 33:39.667
<i>lined up on the
edge of mass graves.</i>

33:45.792 --> 33:48.292
<i>This was not the industrial</i>

33:48.293 --> 33:50.792
<i>horror of Auschwitz.</i>

33:53.709 --> 33:56.499
<i>This was a direct</i>
human being to human

33:56.500 --> 34:01.459
being atrocity.

34:05.375 --> 34:09.876
<i>It concentrated in
a very direct way</i>

34:09.918 --> 34:12.751
<i>the ability of one human being</i>

34:12.792 --> 34:17.083
<i>to savagely destroy another</i>

34:17.125 --> 34:20.500
<i>in a way that is just
incomprehensible.</i>

34:28.417 --> 34:30.833
He said "I'm sorry,
we can't do it."

34:30.876 --> 34:32.938
All the 12 trials have been

34:32.938 --> 34:35.000
approved by the Pentagon.

34:35.042 --> 34:36.958
We have, the staff has

34:36.960 --> 34:38.876
already been assigned.

34:38.918 --> 34:40.313
We don't have staff, we

34:40.315 --> 34:41.708
probably can't get approval

34:41.751 --> 34:43.125
for any more crimes anyway.

34:43.167 --> 34:45.375
The Pentagon had already cooled

34:45.417 --> 34:48.375
"on the trials,
so we can't do it."

34:48.417 --> 34:51.417
"Ah," I said,
"you can't let these guys go.

34:51.458 --> 34:53.043
I have in my hand mass murder

34:53.043 --> 34:54.626
on an incredible scale.

34:54.667 --> 34:56.083
The evidence is all here.

34:56.125 --> 34:58.667
"You're not gonna let
these guys walk away."

34:58.709 --> 35:01.059
- He said, "Well can you do it in.
- Addition to your other work?"

35:01.083 --> 35:02.792
And I said, "Sure!"

35:02.834 --> 35:04.751
And he said "Okay,
so you do it."

35:04.792 --> 35:06.792
Okay, and so it happened that

35:06.793 --> 35:08.792
I became the chief prosecutor

35:08.834 --> 35:11.647
of what turned out to
be the biggest murder

35:11.648 --> 35:12.709
trial in human history.

35:12.751 --> 35:16.876
I have to say looking
back on myself at 27,

35:16.918 --> 35:19.268
- I don't know about you, I.
- Can't think of very many people.

35:19.292 --> 35:23.626
Who would've had the
confidence, the skill,

35:23.667 --> 35:28.667
and the knowledge in
a new legal territory

35:29.792 --> 35:32.876
to be so persuasive
in that role.

35:39.876 --> 35:41.751
<i>First of all, you only pick</i>

35:41.752 --> 35:43.626
<i>a guy who's in captivity.</i>

35:43.667 --> 35:45.272
<i>You don't name Adolf Hitler</i>

35:45.273 --> 35:46.876
<i>'cause you know he's dead,</i>

35:46.918 --> 35:48.918
<i>and there's no sense
putting him in.</i>

35:48.959 --> 35:51.001
<i>So I first said is he dead</i>

35:51.002 --> 35:53.042
<i>or alive, and do we have him?</i>

35:53.083 --> 35:54.959
<i>If we haven't got him, you know.</i>

35:55.000 --> 35:57.167
<i>Mengele and people like
that, forget it.</i>

35:57.209 --> 35:58.209
<i>They may be the top,</i>

35:58.210 --> 35:59.210
<i>but we haven't got 'em.</i>

35:59.250 --> 36:01.500
<i>So you have to know
he's in captivity.</i>

36:06.500 --> 36:08.563
<i>Now, and what evidence</i>

36:08.564 --> 36:10.626
<i>do we have against him?</i>

36:10.667 --> 36:11.727
<i>The Einsatzgruppe was easy.</i>

36:11.751 --> 36:13.125
<i>I had their daily reports.</i>

36:15.250 --> 36:16.792
<i>I had the roster of all the</i>

36:16.793 --> 36:18.334
<i>members of the Einsatzgruppe.</i>

36:18.375 --> 36:20.059
<i>- So I just went through.
- Them and picked me out.</i>

36:20.083 --> 36:22.042
The highest ranking ones,

36:22.083 --> 36:25.209
and so they had about
five or six generals.

36:25.250 --> 36:26.918
I had no enlisted
men in my dock.

36:26.959 --> 36:28.188
Having been an enlisted man

36:28.189 --> 36:29.417
in the United States Army

36:29.459 --> 36:30.959
maybe I was biased.

36:31.000 --> 36:33.167
No enlisted men in my dock.

36:33.209 --> 36:34.480
Give me the highest rank

36:34.481 --> 36:35.751
and the best educated.

36:35.792 --> 36:38.042
<i>Those are the two criteria.</i>

36:40.667 --> 36:43.292
<i>Many of them with
doctor degrees,</i>

36:43.334 --> 36:45.834
<i>doctor,
Dr. Rasch had a double doctorate</i>

36:45.876 --> 36:47.918
<i>and I never had
heard that before.</i>

36:47.959 --> 36:49.042
<i>I was surprised at doctor</i>

36:49.043 --> 36:50.125
<i>doctor, two doctorates.</i>

36:50.167 --> 36:54.209
He killed 33,721
Jews in two days.

36:54.250 --> 36:56.375
29, 30 September, 1941.

36:59.959 --> 37:01.167
I got the bastard.

37:10.417 --> 37:12.876
<i>I was the first
one in the courtroom.</i>

37:16.834 --> 37:18.105
<i>I went in, I sat down,</i>

37:18.106 --> 37:19.375
<i>there was nobody but me.</i>

37:23.792 --> 37:26.042
<i>I was thinking over my statement</i>

37:26.083 --> 37:28.751
<i>which I had written
the day before.</i>

37:28.792 --> 37:30.792
<i>I was seeing if I
could improve it,</i>

37:30.834 --> 37:32.667
<i>and I was waiting for
the trial to begin.</i>

37:36.667 --> 37:37.792
<i>I was calm.</i>

37:38.959 --> 37:40.751
<i>I was determined.</i>

37:42.834 --> 37:45.042
<i>I didn't realize I
would be making history.</i>

37:53.918 --> 37:57.626
We are now ready to
hear the presentation

37:57.627 --> 37:58.792
by the prosecution.

37:58.834 --> 38:00.542
<i>I made the opening statement,</i>

38:00.543 --> 38:02.250
<i>which stated the case.</i>

38:02.292 --> 38:04.250
<i>It did not appear on the film,</i>

38:04.292 --> 38:06.459
because the film
didn't start rolling

38:06.500 --> 38:07.688
until after the first

38:07.689 --> 38:08.876
paragraph had been done,

38:08.918 --> 38:10.251
and what it left out was

38:10.252 --> 38:11.584
the important beginning.

38:11.626 --> 38:13.626
It was,
"May it please your honors,"

38:13.667 --> 38:15.876
it is with sorrow and with hope

38:15.918 --> 38:18.250
that we here disclose
the massive murder

38:18.292 --> 38:20.167
"of a million people et cetera."

38:21.792 --> 38:23.667
This was the tragic fulfillment

38:25.042 --> 38:28.751
of a program of
intolerance and arrogance.

38:28.792 --> 38:30.292
<i>But I was very specific.</i>

38:30.334 --> 38:32.459
Vengeance is not our goal.

38:33.667 --> 38:37.167
Nor do we seek merely
a just retribution.

38:38.334 --> 38:40.626
We ask this court to affirm

38:40.627 --> 38:42.918
by international penal action

38:44.834 --> 38:48.125
man's right to live
in peace and dignity

38:49.167 --> 38:51.334
regardless of his race or creed.

38:53.500 --> 38:56.000
The case we present is a

38:56.001 --> 38:58.500
plea of humanity to law.

39:00.167 --> 39:02.709
<i>So here at 27,
I don't know about you,</i>

39:02.751 --> 39:05.334
27 is just the beginning
of being a grownup

39:05.375 --> 39:07.876
and he was in
front of the world.

39:07.918 --> 39:09.501
He wasn't just in front of these

39:09.502 --> 39:11.083
judges and these defendants.

39:11.125 --> 39:12.834
He was in front of the world

39:12.876 --> 39:14.751
making a case as a prosecutor.

39:14.792 --> 39:16.918
Looking at the judges and saying

39:16.959 --> 39:19.334
the case we present is a

39:19.335 --> 39:22.709
plea of humanity to
law, beautiful stuff.

39:22.751 --> 39:25.584
Honestly, it was years for me

39:25.626 --> 39:27.022
before I wouldn't get literally

39:27.023 --> 39:28.417
teary eyed and emotional

39:28.459 --> 39:29.918
just saying those words

39:29.919 --> 39:32.876
because I think
they're so powerful, so

39:29.959 --> 39:32.876
beautiful, so applicable,

39:32.918 --> 39:34.375
so apropos to what's
happening today.

39:34.417 --> 39:37.126
We shall show that these

39:37.127 --> 39:39.834
deeds of men in uniform

39:39.876 --> 39:42.355
for the methodical execution

39:42.356 --> 39:44.834
of long range plans

39:44.876 --> 39:47.584
to destroy ethnic, national,

39:47.585 --> 39:50.292
political, and religious groups

39:51.542 --> 39:54.250
which stood condemned
in the Nazi mind.

39:55.876 --> 39:59.876
<i>Here's Ben standing
on some books</i>

39:59.918 --> 40:03.834
<i>so that he can be
taller than the lectern</i>

40:03.876 --> 40:07.042
that is immediately
in front of him.

40:07.083 --> 40:08.729
I can only imagine what

40:08.730 --> 40:10.375
he must have felt like here.

40:10.417 --> 40:11.792
This little Jewish guy who,

40:11.793 --> 40:13.167
had his parents not left,

40:13.209 --> 40:14.584
would've been one of

40:14.585 --> 40:15.959
those gassed and killed,

40:16.000 --> 40:18.334
standing and looking at

40:18.335 --> 40:22.168
these German supermen
<i>and saying "I have</i>"

40:22.169 --> 40:25.125
<i>more power now,
but I'm just a kid."</i>

40:25.167 --> 40:27.417
<i>It must have been
such a mixed feeling</i>

40:27.459 --> 40:29.855
of passion and determination,

40:29.856 --> 40:32.250
"I have to do this,"

40:32.292 --> 40:35.250
and nervousness
and a combination

40:35.292 --> 40:37.292
<i>of self-confidence
and self-doubt.</i>

40:39.500 --> 40:41.751
<i>I wasn't nervous at all.</i>

40:41.792 --> 40:42.959
<i>I didn't kill anybody.</i>

40:43.000 --> 40:44.667
<i>They were the ones
who were nervous,</i>

40:44.709 --> 40:46.126
<i>and they should have been</i>

40:46.127 --> 40:47.542
<i>'cause I had the evidence.</i>

40:48.918 --> 40:50.209
You know this was really

40:50.210 --> 40:51.500
every prosecutor's dream.

40:51.542 --> 40:52.768
You don't have to
call a witness.

40:52.792 --> 40:55.292
All you have to do is
enter the documents,

40:55.334 --> 40:57.063
primary documents saying when,

40:57.064 --> 40:58.792
where, who did the killing.

41:00.543 --> 41:02.250
<i>Because you had enough written</i>

41:02.251 --> 41:04.792
<i>documentary material
that you could point</i>

41:02.292 --> 41:04.792
<i>at saying, "Yeah."</i>

41:04.834 --> 41:07.209
Here you say,
"Is this your signature?"

41:07.250 --> 41:09.125
And that's it.

41:09.167 --> 41:10.938
You didn't need to have any

41:10.939 --> 41:12.709
more proof by witnesses.

41:13.500 --> 41:15.792
And of course the Germans

41:15.793 --> 41:18.792
were cautious enough
to put everything into

41:15.834 --> 41:18.792
the books that they did.

41:20.584 --> 41:23.292
And offered as
prosecution exhibit 29,

41:26.834 --> 41:28.751
I see there's another
objection coming.

41:28.792 --> 41:29.792
I'll continue the quote.

41:38.209 --> 41:39.792
<i>The defense lawyers</i>

41:39.793 --> 41:41.375
<i>who were generally German</i>

41:41.417 --> 41:43.230
were actually a highly

41:43.231 --> 41:45.042
talented group of lawyers,

41:45.083 --> 41:47.125
and they bore themselves

41:47.126 --> 41:49.167
quite well in the courtroom

41:49.209 --> 41:51.751
and they sometimes
were able to challenge

41:51.792 --> 41:54.542
the prosecution
quite effectively.

41:54.584 --> 41:57.792
They were very much
individualists,

41:57.834 --> 41:59.917
and they didn't come up with

41:59.918 --> 42:02.000
a sort of common strategy.

42:02.042 --> 42:03.792
They all had their
own strategies.

42:03.834 --> 42:08.292
<i>They were paid by the tribunal,</i>

42:08.334 --> 42:10.709
<i>and for the times then</i>

42:10.751 --> 42:12.584
<i>it was a considerable
amount of money.</i>

42:12.626 --> 42:14.376
You know, in 1945 Germany

42:14.377 --> 42:16.125
was totally destructed

42:16.167 --> 42:17.751
and for a lawyer I think it

42:17.752 --> 42:19.334
was quite a good thing to,

42:19.375 --> 42:21.105
to work at the tribunal because

42:21.106 --> 42:24.083
you were given money
on a regular basis.

42:24.125 --> 42:26.522
It should be recognized

42:26.523 --> 42:30.855
that in 1945 and '46,
the German people

42:30.856 --> 42:34.272
were not necessarily
<i>seeking to tarnish</i>

42:34.273 --> 42:37.876
<i>the reputation of
their surviving</i>

42:37.877 --> 42:39.959
<i>leaders at that time.</i>

42:40.000 --> 42:41.834
<i>There was a lot of
opposition to Nuremberg</i>

42:41.876 --> 42:44.083
<i>by the German
people, and so when</i>

42:44.125 --> 42:46.292
<i>they saw their leaders
up on the stand</i>

42:46.334 --> 42:49.250
<i>this was an assault
on German honor.</i>

42:49.292 --> 42:52.709
And so you know the
defense lawyers knew

42:52.751 --> 42:54.793
that they sort of had the

42:54.794 --> 42:56.834
German people behind them

42:56.876 --> 42:59.230
in representing the Nazi

42:59.231 --> 43:01.584
defendants on the stand.

43:03.000 --> 43:05.000
Have you read the indictment?

43:05.042 --> 43:06.250
Yeah.

43:06.292 --> 43:08.209
How do you plead
to this indictment?

43:08.250 --> 43:09.667
Guilty or not guilty?

43:13.834 --> 43:15.751
"Not guilty in the
sense of the indictment"

43:15.792 --> 43:18.709
is what they said,
but what did that mean?

43:18.751 --> 43:19.935
The judge said correctly,
"We'll take that

43:19.959 --> 43:21.584
as a plea of not guilty."

43:21.626 --> 43:24.876
I think the defendants
honestly believed

43:24.918 --> 43:27.083
they were not guilty.

43:27.125 --> 43:29.709
They had persuaded themselves

43:29.710 --> 43:32.292
that they did the right thing.

43:32.334 --> 43:35.876
<i>These were people who were</i>

43:35.918 --> 43:38.064
<i>not necessarily born to</i>

43:38.065 --> 43:40.209
<i>become mass murderers.</i>

43:40.250 --> 43:43.626
<i>They were susceptible
to the pressures</i>

43:43.667 --> 43:45.688
<i>that made them mass</i>

43:45.689 --> 43:47.709
<i>murderers in the Nazi regime.</i>

43:47.751 --> 43:48.876
That doesn't mean that

43:48.877 --> 43:50.000
I could ever do that.

43:50.042 --> 43:51.268
I could never do that, no matter

43:51.292 --> 43:52.918
what the circumstances were.

43:52.959 --> 43:54.855
There are certain people who

43:54.856 --> 43:56.751
could never, ever become Nazis

43:56.792 --> 43:57.938
and there are others who

43:57.939 --> 43:59.083
could've gone either way

43:59.125 --> 44:00.376
and I think many of the

44:00.377 --> 44:01.626
defendants at Nuremberg

44:01.667 --> 44:04.626
could have gone either way.

44:18.334 --> 44:23.083
<i>Dr. Otto Ohlendorf,
General of the SS.</i>

44:23.125 --> 44:24.709
<i>I knew him quite well.</i>

44:24.751 --> 44:27.876
Now, would I call him an animal?

44:27.918 --> 44:29.876
He was rational.

44:29.918 --> 44:32.709
He was I'm sure good
to his cats and dogs.

44:32.751 --> 44:34.167
He was the father
of five children.

44:34.209 --> 44:36.918
<i>He made a sensible argument.</i>

44:36.959 --> 44:40.626
<i>He was reasonably
honest in his answers.</i>

44:40.667 --> 44:42.792
<i>He said he would do it again,</i>

44:42.834 --> 44:44.293
<i>even if they ordered him</i>

44:44.294 --> 44:45.751
<i>to kill his own sister</i>

44:45.792 --> 44:47.834
<i>and the reason was Hitler</i>

44:47.835 --> 44:51.314
<i>knew that the Germans
were going to be</i>

44:51.315 --> 44:52.709
<i>attacked by the Russians</i>

44:52.751 --> 44:54.918
<i>and Hitler had more
knowledge than he did,</i>

44:54.959 --> 44:56.355
<i>therefore he was in no</i>

44:56.356 --> 44:57.751
<i>position to challenge that.</i>

44:57.792 --> 45:01.000
<i>And it was lawful,
therefore to act</i>

45:01.042 --> 45:03.397
in anticipatory self-defense

45:03.398 --> 45:05.751
to prevent that from happening

45:05.792 --> 45:07.334
and that's what he was doing.

45:07.375 --> 45:09.542
<i>He made an argument which the.</i>

45:09.543 --> 45:11.709
<i>Pentagon would make today.</i>

45:13.000 --> 45:15.209
<i>Self-defense was his plea.</i>

45:17.167 --> 45:19.043
Very well, we'll leave

45:19.044 --> 45:20.918
this after one more question.

45:20.959 --> 45:23.126
The figure of 90,000 is the

45:23.127 --> 45:25.292
best estimate you can give

45:27.959 --> 45:28.959
at this moment.

45:29.918 --> 45:32.375
I take it we must
continue to read that

45:32.417 --> 45:34.771
with the qualification which

45:34.772 --> 45:37.125
you gave in direct testimony

45:37.167 --> 45:39.417
that you think there's a great

45:39.418 --> 45:41.667
deal of exaggeration in it.

45:42.876 --> 45:44.959
<i>He made the point,
some of the commanders</i>

45:45.000 --> 45:46.813
would take the infants

45:46.814 --> 45:49.709
and just hold 'em by
a leg and smash their

45:49.710 --> 45:51.855
head against a tree
and he said I didn't

45:51.856 --> 45:52.918
believe in that.

45:52.959 --> 45:54.834
He said, "I told my men"

45:54.835 --> 45:56.709
when a mother has an infant

45:56.751 --> 45:58.751
and of course the
infant is crying

45:58.792 --> 46:00.250
and the mother is crying

46:00.292 --> 46:03.584
and she's holding the
infant to her breast,

46:03.626 --> 46:05.126
aim for the infant because

46:05.127 --> 46:06.626
you'll kill both of them

46:06.667 --> 46:08.709
with one shot,
you'll quiet the mother,

46:08.751 --> 46:10.272
<i>you'll save ammunition</i>

46:10.273 --> 46:11.792
<i>"and it's much more humane."</i>

46:13.751 --> 46:14.709
<i>"And there were other things."</i>

46:14.751 --> 46:16.792
<i>For example, we had gas vans.</i>

46:16.834 --> 46:18.272
<i>They were ordinary, you</i>

46:18.273 --> 46:19.709
<i>know, like trailers here</i>

46:19.751 --> 46:21.647
<i>except that they attached</i>

46:21.648 --> 46:23.542
<i>the hose from the engine</i>

46:23.584 --> 46:25.876
<i>to the inside so the fumes would</i>

46:25.918 --> 46:28.918
<i>asphyxiate the people
inside the van,</i>

46:28.959 --> 46:31.000
<i>and they'd pack 'em in
solid, lock 'em in,</i>

46:31.042 --> 46:32.918
<i>and about 20 minutes
they get to the place</i>

46:32.959 --> 46:34.042
<i>where they're going to</i>

46:34.043 --> 46:36.459
<i>dump 'em,
open the van and dump 'em all</i>

46:35.167 --> 46:36.459
<i>"into the ditch."</i>

46:36.500 --> 46:37.875
But Ohlendorf said,

46:37.876 --> 46:40.688
"I didn't like the gas
vans because some of"

46:40.689 --> 46:43.959
them were not dead,
and then you had to

46:42.125 --> 46:43.959
sort 'em out by hand

46:44.000 --> 46:45.438
and they were screaming

46:45.439 --> 46:48.314
"and they were bloody
and they were messy,"

46:48.315 --> 46:49.709
and he said, "it was bad"

46:49.751 --> 46:50.959
for the morale of the

46:50.960 --> 46:52.167
men to have to do that.

46:52.209 --> 46:53.751
So I told 'em I didn't want

46:53.752 --> 46:55.292
"any more of the gas vans."

46:55.334 --> 46:57.043
So Ohlendorf was really

46:57.044 --> 46:58.791
quite a decent
chap, you might say,

46:58.792 --> 47:00.334
aside from the fact

47:00.375 --> 47:02.166
that he killed 90,000
Jews, I'm sure he was

47:02.167 --> 47:03.918
quite a gentleman.

47:15.250 --> 47:17.042
<i>These million
people were murdered</i>

47:17.083 --> 47:18.792
<i>because they didn't share</i>

47:18.793 --> 47:21.959
<i>the race, the religion,
or the ideology of</i>

47:21.960 --> 47:24.876
<i>"their executioners,
and I said, "That's</i>

47:24.877 --> 47:27.500
<i>a terrible crime
and it's a crime</i>

47:24.918 --> 47:27.500
<i>"against humanity."</i>

47:27.542 --> 47:29.834
<i>And I called it a
crime against humanity.</i>

47:32.918 --> 47:34.022
<i>"And I said," If we can</i>

47:34.023 --> 47:37.792
<i>prevent that in future
by condemning crimes</i>

47:37.793 --> 47:40.792
<i>against humanity,
we will reassert the</i>

47:40.793 --> 47:42.876
<i>"legal right of all
people to be protected."</i>

47:46.250 --> 47:48.334
<i>If we could establish
a principle rule</i>

47:48.375 --> 47:51.626
<i>which would protect
humanity in the future,</i>

47:51.667 --> 47:54.083
<i>then this trial
would be significant.</i>

47:59.918 --> 48:01.459
For the first time, the

48:01.460 --> 48:03.000
international community

48:03.042 --> 48:07.542
tried to put law as an answer

48:07.584 --> 48:09.959
to these most horrible crimes

48:10.000 --> 48:12.834
<i>that originated
from Nazi Germany.</i>

48:12.876 --> 48:14.751
<i>And this was a revolution.</i>

48:14.792 --> 48:17.250
<i>It started the
way we think about</i>

48:17.292 --> 48:19.250
international criminal law.

48:19.292 --> 48:21.042
About international
law generally.

48:23.209 --> 48:27.375
<i>I had a list I made
myself on a yellow page</i>

48:27.417 --> 48:28.876
<i>in which I listed
all the defendants</i>

48:28.918 --> 48:30.501
<i>and I listed what I thought</i>

48:30.502 --> 48:32.083
<i>the sentence should be.</i>

48:33.250 --> 48:36.042
The actual sentences
were more severe

48:36.083 --> 48:37.751
than what I would have listed.

48:40.584 --> 48:41.584
<i>I was numb.</i>

48:43.000 --> 48:44.563
<i>They're all imprisoned</i>

48:44.564 --> 48:46.125
<i>below the courthouse.</i>

48:46.167 --> 48:48.500
<i>There is a lift,
Black Maria they called</i>

48:48.542 --> 48:49.792
<i>which keeps going around</i>

48:49.793 --> 48:51.042
<i>into the courthouse</i>

48:51.083 --> 48:53.292
<i>and a sliding door which opens.</i>

48:53.334 --> 48:56.125
<i>As each defendant came up,</i>

48:56.167 --> 48:58.792
<i>they would hear the judge,</i>

48:58.834 --> 49:01.042
<i>"For the crimes of
which you are convicted,"</i>

49:01.083 --> 49:02.625
<i>this tribunal sentenced</i>

49:02.626 --> 49:04.167
<i>"you to death by hanging."</i>

49:05.626 --> 49:08.834
Put the earphones
back, take it off.

49:08.876 --> 49:10.918
Bow, step back a
step into the lift,

49:10.959 --> 49:12.667
the door closes, and he

49:12.668 --> 49:14.375
drops down into hell.

49:14.417 --> 49:15.792
That's what I saw.

49:17.125 --> 49:18.376
One after the other,

49:18.377 --> 49:19.626
for the crimes of which

49:19.667 --> 49:21.626
you are convicted, this tribunal

49:21.667 --> 49:22.855
sentences you death by

49:22.856 --> 49:24.042
hanging, death by hanging,

49:24.083 --> 49:25.500
death by hanging.

49:25.542 --> 49:27.292
I thought my head
was gonna bust.

49:28.918 --> 49:31.626
<i>It was customary for
the chief prosecutor</i>

49:31.667 --> 49:33.230
<i>to invite his staff for a party</i>

49:33.231 --> 49:34.792
<i>when every trial was ended.</i>

49:34.834 --> 49:36.500
<i>I had a party
arranged for my house.</i>

49:36.542 --> 49:38.375
<i>I couldn't go to my own party.</i>

49:38.417 --> 49:40.167
<i>I went home, went to bed.</i>

49:40.209 --> 49:42.792
<i>My head was pounding with it.</i>

49:44.042 --> 49:45.876
<i>So how do you describe</i>

49:45.877 --> 49:47.709
<i>that emotion, that feeling?</i>

49:47.751 --> 49:49.626
<i>I didn't say I'm sorry for them.</i>

49:49.667 --> 49:50.959
<i>I didn't say hooray for me.</i>

49:52.542 --> 49:55.063
<i>It was a very tense, very</i>

49:55.064 --> 49:57.584
<i>severe emotional reaction</i>

49:58.667 --> 50:00.948
<i>- knowing that you're responsible.
- For killing this guy.</i>

50:02.792 --> 50:05.918
<i>Otto Ohlendorf,
he was the only defendant</i>

50:05.959 --> 50:10.709
<i>that I ever talked to man to man</i>

50:10.751 --> 50:12.542
<i>after he was sentenced to death.</i>

50:13.792 --> 50:15.626
<i>I felt, look, this guy</i>

50:15.627 --> 50:17.459
<i>is gonna hang for sure.</i>

50:18.626 --> 50:20.418
<i>He's the father of five</i>

50:20.419 --> 50:22.209
<i>kids, he has a wife,</i>

50:22.250 --> 50:24.083
<i>he was honest on the trial.</i>

50:24.125 --> 50:25.792
<i>Maybe he'll tell me something,</i>

50:25.834 --> 50:27.918
<i>you know tell my
children I love them,</i>

50:27.959 --> 50:29.709
<i>tell my wife I'm sorry.</i>

50:29.751 --> 50:32.792
<i>Nobody ever said
they were sorry.</i>

50:32.834 --> 50:35.417
<i>So I went down to talk to him,</i>

50:35.459 --> 50:37.876
<i>and he's locked up in a cell</i>

50:37.918 --> 50:40.584
<i>behind bars under the courthouse</i>

50:40.626 --> 50:43.792
<i>and a little window opens up,</i>

50:43.834 --> 50:47.918
<i>and I said to him.</i>

50:47.959 --> 50:50.209
<i>"Can I do something for you?"</i>

50:50.250 --> 50:52.417
<i>AND THEN HE BEGAN:</i>

50:52.418 --> 50:54.584
<i>"You'll see I was right."</i>

50:54.626 --> 50:57.959
The Russians are gonna
take over the Jews.

50:58.000 --> 51:00.042
"The Jews in America
will suffer."

51:00.083 --> 51:02.041
and he just goes
repeating the argument he

51:02.042 --> 51:03.792
read on the trial.

51:03.834 --> 51:06.459
I let him go for about a minute,

51:06.500 --> 51:08.126
and then I said, "Goodbye."

51:08.127 --> 51:09.751
"Mr. Ohlendorf" in English,

51:09.792 --> 51:11.292
closed the door and left.

51:11.334 --> 51:13.022
<i>The next thing I saw I was</i>

51:13.023 --> 51:14.709
<i>invited to come to the hanging.</i>

51:14.751 --> 51:16.168
<i>I refused to go, but they</i>

51:16.169 --> 51:17.584
<i>sent me the tape anyway</i>

51:17.626 --> 51:18.772
<i>so I have a picture of</i>

51:18.773 --> 51:19.918
<i>him hanging by the neck</i>

51:19.959 --> 51:22.626
<i>for eight minutes and
then pronounced dead.</i>

51:33.375 --> 51:35.729
<i>I wanted to go home, but then</i>

51:35.730 --> 51:38.083
<i>something terrible happened.</i>

51:39.792 --> 51:41.667
<i>I was approached by
Jewish organizations</i>

51:41.709 --> 51:43.042
and they said, "Hey boy",

51:45.626 --> 51:46.768
there's something
else to be done here.

51:46.792 --> 51:47.959
"What about the victims?"

51:48.042 --> 51:50.209
<i>And it didn't take
long to convince me</i>

51:50.250 --> 51:52.542
<i>they had managed to get a</i>

51:52.543 --> 51:54.834
<i>military government law enacted</i>

51:54.876 --> 51:57.334
<i>saying that the property
of murdered Jews</i>

51:57.375 --> 52:00.250
<i>would go not to
the German state,</i>

52:00.292 --> 52:03.292
<i>but to a consortium of
Jewish organizations</i>

52:03.334 --> 52:05.105
<i>which would use it for charity</i>

52:05.106 --> 52:06.876
<i>purposes of the survivors</i>

52:06.918 --> 52:09.792
and that sounded like
a very good idea,

52:09.834 --> 52:11.709
except they wanted
me to take it over

52:11.751 --> 52:13.083
and to do the job.

52:13.125 --> 52:14.813
<i>"I said," How long do</i>

52:14.814 --> 52:16.500
<i>they think it'll take?"</i>

52:16.542 --> 52:18.084
<i>They said, "Well, we'd like</i>

52:18.085 --> 52:19.626
<i>a commitment of two years."</i>

52:19.667 --> 52:21.792
<i>Well I went back
to my dear wife,</i>

52:21.834 --> 52:23.647
<i>"and she said," Well the</i>

52:23.648 --> 52:26.521
<i>cause seems good enough,
but they said two</i>

52:26.522 --> 52:27.542
<i>years but if I know you</i>

52:27.584 --> 52:29.792
<i>it'll only take one year.</i>

52:29.834 --> 52:31.334
<i>"So take the job."</i>

52:31.375 --> 52:34.542
Whereupon,
being the sole employee,

52:34.584 --> 52:36.542
I declared myself
the director general

52:36.584 --> 52:39.542
<i>and set about to recover</i>

52:39.584 --> 52:41.709
<i>the heirless unclaimed
Jewish property.</i>

52:41.751 --> 52:44.584
<i>Naturally,
the cemeteries were unclaimed</i>

52:44.626 --> 52:46.667
<i>because the Jewish
congregations which had</i>

52:46.709 --> 52:48.126
<i>built up these cemeteries</i>

52:48.127 --> 52:49.542
<i>for centuries were gone.</i>

52:49.584 --> 52:51.792
They were abolished,
and the cemeteries

52:51.834 --> 52:54.042
became property of the Reich.

52:54.083 --> 52:56.751
<i>So I immediately
asserted ownership</i>

52:56.792 --> 53:00.230
<i>of all these cemeteries
on behalf of the</i>

53:00.231 --> 53:01.417
<i>successor organization.</i>

53:02.834 --> 53:04.709
<i>All well and good,</i>

53:04.710 --> 53:06.584
<i>except the question arose</i>

53:06.626 --> 53:08.418
<i>who pays the course of the</i>

53:08.419 --> 53:10.209
<i>maintenance of the cemeteries?</i>

53:10.250 --> 53:12.417
<i>Hundreds of cemeteries.</i>

53:15.834 --> 53:17.022
<i>The Polish government</i>

53:17.023 --> 53:18.209
<i>and the Polish Red Cross</i>

53:18.250 --> 53:20.751
invited me to come to Poland

53:20.792 --> 53:23.959
and be their guest for a week.

53:24.000 --> 53:25.334
I said, "The only thing I really"

53:25.375 --> 53:26.768
wanted to see in
Poland was Auschwitz

53:26.792 --> 53:28.751
because I'd never been there

53:28.792 --> 53:30.512
"and it had been liberated
by the Russians."

53:33.083 --> 53:35.583
<i>The field behind Auschwitz</i>

53:35.584 --> 53:38.083
<i>is covered with wild grass.</i>

53:40.751 --> 53:42.792
<i>And under the grass,</i>

