<i>Robert McNamara, the</i>

01:05:49.168 --> 01:05:51.500
<i>architect of the Vietnam War.</i>

01:05:52.834 --> 01:05:54.751
<i>My response to him in</i>

01:05:54.752 --> 01:05:56.125
<i>practically these
words I'm sure,</i>

01:05:56.167 --> 01:05:58.918
<i>"Mr.
Secretary I think you realize"</i>

01:05:58.959 --> 01:06:00.876
<i>that if we had such a court,</i>

01:06:00.918 --> 01:06:03.792
<i>"you might be one of
the first defendants."</i>

01:06:03.834 --> 01:06:05.626
<i>He said I know that.</i>

01:06:05.667 --> 01:06:06.834
<i>I said then why do you ask me</i>

01:06:06.876 --> 01:06:09.751
<i>to get the United
States to sign on?</i>

01:06:09.792 --> 01:06:11.626
<i>He said,
"I didn't know it was illegal."</i>

01:06:11.667 --> 01:06:13.292
<i>we're talking the Vietnam War.</i>

01:06:13.334 --> 01:06:15.751
"If I had known,
I wouldn't have done it."

01:06:15.792 --> 01:06:17.230
I said, "Okay."

01:06:17.231 --> 01:06:18.667
I drafted the letter.

01:06:18.709 --> 01:06:23.751
That was a very
powerful partnership

01:06:23.792 --> 01:06:26.751
and you bet President
Bill Clinton

01:06:26.792 --> 01:06:28.083
would read that op-ed.

01:06:30.584 --> 01:06:32.459
<i>And if there's anything
anyone should know</i>

01:06:32.500 --> 01:06:33.876
<i>about president Clinton is</i>

01:06:33.918 --> 01:06:35.001
<i>he actually makes decisions</i>

01:06:35.002 --> 01:06:36.083
<i>at the last moment.</i>

01:06:36.125 --> 01:06:39.021
He makes good decisions,
but he does wait

01:06:39.022 --> 01:06:40.250
until the last moment,

01:06:40.292 --> 01:06:41.813
and so he did finally

01:06:41.814 --> 01:06:43.334
reach that decision early

01:06:43.375 --> 01:06:47.751
<i>of December 31st and
I was authorized then</i>

01:06:47.792 --> 01:06:49.667
<i>to go to New York
and sign the treaty.</i>

01:06:51.375 --> 01:06:53.792
Well on December
30th I receive a call

01:06:53.834 --> 01:06:57.042
<i>instructing me to
get a train ticket</i>

01:06:57.083 --> 01:06:58.771
<i>for the next morning on Amtrak</i>

01:06:58.772 --> 01:07:02.292
<i>so that I'm in New
York, and it happened to</i>

01:07:00.500 --> 01:07:02.292
<i>be a huge snowstorm</i>

01:07:02.334 --> 01:07:03.897
<i>"but they said," The President</i>

01:07:03.898 --> 01:07:05.459
<i>has not made a decision yet,</i>

01:07:05.500 --> 01:07:07.000
"but we want you on that train,"

01:07:07.042 --> 01:07:08.000
because there were no flights.

01:07:08.042 --> 01:07:10.250
The weather was preventing that.

01:07:10.292 --> 01:07:12.230
<i>"You'll receive instructions</i>

01:07:12.231 --> 01:07:14.167
<i>when you arrive in New York,"</i>

01:07:14.209 --> 01:07:16.167
<i>and I finally got
to Penn Station</i>

01:07:16.209 --> 01:07:18.230
and I still had not received

01:07:18.231 --> 01:07:20.250
the final instruction.

01:07:20.292 --> 01:07:24.542
I'm riding up the
escalator at Penn Station

01:07:24.584 --> 01:07:26.272
<i>and I receive a call from</i>

01:07:26.273 --> 01:07:27.959
<i>the Secretary of State,</i>

01:07:28.000 --> 01:07:30.876
<i>Madeleine Albright, my boss.</i>

01:07:30.918 --> 01:07:32.835
<i>She informed me that the</i>

01:07:32.836 --> 01:07:34.751
<i>president had made the decision</i>

01:07:34.792 --> 01:07:36.375
that the treaty would be signed

01:07:36.417 --> 01:07:37.918
and that I had authority now

01:07:37.959 --> 01:07:39.376
to proceed to the United.

01:07:39.377 --> 01:07:40.792
Nations to sign the document.

01:07:40.834 --> 01:07:42.438
<i>New York City was</i>

01:07:42.439 --> 01:07:44.042
<i>completely covered by snow.</i>

01:07:44.083 --> 01:07:46.209
<i>There were no taxis running,</i>

01:07:46.210 --> 01:07:48.334
<i>and so I had my snow boots on</i>

01:07:48.375 --> 01:07:49.584
<i>and I hiked from Penn Station</i>

01:07:49.585 --> 01:07:50.792
<i>to the United Nations.</i>

01:07:50.834 --> 01:07:53.042
<i>The UN had to open just for me</i>

01:07:53.083 --> 01:07:55.667
<i>to walk in and sign the treaty,</i>

01:07:55.709 --> 01:07:56.810
<i>because it was closed that day.</i>

01:07:56.834 --> 01:07:58.209
<i>It was New Year's Eve.</i>

01:07:58.250 --> 01:07:59.959
<i>They close at the UN.</i>

01:08:00.000 --> 01:08:02.438
<i>And I walked in to the room</i>

01:08:02.439 --> 01:08:04.876
<i>where treaties are signed,</i>

01:08:04.918 --> 01:08:06.689
and there was a very small

01:08:06.690 --> 01:08:08.459
group of people to witness it.

01:08:08.500 --> 01:08:11.209
Very interesting.

01:08:11.250 --> 01:08:13.042
The last official act of the.

01:08:13.043 --> 01:08:14.834
President of the United States

01:08:14.876 --> 01:08:17.082
when is everybody sound asleep

01:08:17.125 --> 01:08:19.584
and he has his ambassador
go sneak in there

01:08:19.626 --> 01:08:20.706
and sign the goddamn thing.

01:08:23.876 --> 01:08:25.751
<i>Unfortunately what George W.
Bush did</i>

01:08:25.792 --> 01:08:27.709
<i>was that he said,
"with respect to that</i>"

01:08:27.751 --> 01:08:30.500
<i>signature on the
treaty, we're no longer</i>

01:08:30.542 --> 01:08:32.334
<i>going to perform our obligation</i>

01:08:32.335 --> 01:08:34.125
<i>"as a signatory state."</i>

01:08:34.167 --> 01:08:36.626
So that was the
downslide after the

01:08:36.667 --> 01:08:38.709
Clinton administration,
much to my regret.

01:08:38.751 --> 01:08:41.500
And that's the
political process.

01:08:41.542 --> 01:08:43.459
Or as Churchill's
reported to have said,

01:08:43.500 --> 01:08:45.395
"It's a terrible system, but he

01:08:45.397 --> 01:08:47.292
can't think of a better one."

01:09:13.751 --> 01:09:15.604
<i>When we started this, every</i>

01:09:15.606 --> 01:09:17.459
<i>time we met with a UN leader</i>

01:09:17.500 --> 01:09:19.292
<i>or a government they said.</i>

01:09:19.292 --> 01:09:21.584
<i>"We'll work on this</i>
but it'll never happen,

01:09:21.585 --> 01:09:23.459
not in your
lifetime, not in your

01:09:21.626 --> 01:09:23.459
"children's lifetime,"

01:09:23.500 --> 01:09:25.126
and less than four years

01:09:25.127 --> 01:09:26.751
later we had a treaty.

01:09:26.792 --> 01:09:28.584
Then we were told the treaty

01:09:28.585 --> 01:09:30.375
would take 20, 25 years

01:09:30.417 --> 01:09:31.709
like the law of the sea

01:09:31.710 --> 01:09:33.000
to get 60 ratification.

01:09:33.042 --> 01:09:34.792
<i>Again,
four years later we had that.</i>

01:09:36.542 --> 01:09:40.292
<i>It is simply not
plausible anymore to argue</i>

01:09:40.334 --> 01:09:44.167
that any political
or military leader

01:09:44.209 --> 01:09:46.688
who is responsible for the

01:09:46.689 --> 01:09:49.167
commission of atrocity crimes

01:09:49.209 --> 01:09:51.375
has the right to
get away with it.

01:09:51.417 --> 01:09:53.751
<i>Nuremberg started that process.</i>

01:09:53.792 --> 01:09:56.459
<i>We got detracted
by the Cold War.</i>

01:09:56.500 --> 01:09:58.146
<i>The Cold War ended, we</i>

01:09:58.147 --> 01:09:59.792
<i>regenerated the process</i>

01:09:59.834 --> 01:10:01.751
<i>in order to hold these</i>

01:10:01.752 --> 01:10:04.730
<i>individuals responsible
and to send a loud</i>

01:10:04.731 --> 01:10:07.646
<i>and clear signal</i>
you are subject to

01:10:07.647 --> 01:10:09.500
criminal law, period

01:10:09.542 --> 01:10:10.647
and you cannot negotiate

01:10:10.648 --> 01:10:11.751
your way out of it.

01:10:13.792 --> 01:10:15.292
May it please your honors,

01:10:16.959 --> 01:10:20.209
this is a historic
moment in the evolution

01:10:20.250 --> 01:10:22.500
of international criminal law.

01:10:23.834 --> 01:10:25.688
For the first time a permanent

01:10:25.689 --> 01:10:27.542
international criminal court

01:10:27.584 --> 01:10:29.730
will hear the closing statement

01:10:29.731 --> 01:10:31.876
for the prosecution

01:10:31.918 --> 01:10:34.375
and it concludes its first case

01:10:34.417 --> 01:10:36.480
against its first accused,

01:10:36.481 --> 01:10:38.542
Mr. Thomas Lubanga Dyilo.

01:10:39.792 --> 01:10:42.167
<i>When the court finally
gets its first case,</i>

01:10:42.209 --> 01:10:43.667
<i>they asked me to do the closing</i>

01:10:43.668 --> 01:10:45.125
<i>statement I'm 92 years old.</i>

01:10:46.667 --> 01:10:47.917
<i>This is against a guy who had</i>

01:10:47.918 --> 01:10:49.167
<i>been using child soldiers.</i>

01:10:50.417 --> 01:10:52.268
<i>- They go and say, "You give.
- Us food, give us money,".</i>

01:10:52.292 --> 01:10:53.396
<i>And if you have no money</i>

01:10:53.397 --> 01:10:54.500
<i>to give them and no food</i>

01:10:54.542 --> 01:10:56.727
<i>- they go, "Oh you got a couple.
- Of kids, we'll take the kids,".</i>

01:10:56.751 --> 01:11:00.125
<i>And they were taking kids 13, 14</i>

01:11:00.167 --> 01:11:01.976
<i>- and the boys they taught.
- 'em how to use a gun.</i>

01:11:02.000 --> 01:11:04.250
<i>The kids loved the
excitement of that,</i>

01:11:04.292 --> 01:11:05.542
<i>and they taught 'em how to kill</i>

01:11:05.584 --> 01:11:07.500
<i>and that happens
to be a war crime.</i>

01:11:08.626 --> 01:11:10.334
<i>When the statute
that binds this court</i>

01:11:10.375 --> 01:11:13.417
was overwhelmingly approved,

01:11:14.584 --> 01:11:17.626
over 100 sovereign
states decided

01:11:17.667 --> 01:11:20.792
<i>that child recruitment
and forcing them</i>

01:11:20.834 --> 01:11:23.834
to participate in
hostilities were

01:11:23.876 --> 01:11:25.709
and I'm quoting now
from the statute,

01:11:25.751 --> 01:11:29.209
"among the most serious
crimes of concern

01:11:29.250 --> 01:11:30.750
<i>"for the international</i>

01:11:30.751 --> 01:11:32.250
<i>community as a whole."</i>

01:11:32.292 --> 01:11:34.584
<i>This was the first ICC case,</i>

01:11:34.626 --> 01:11:37.876
and I believe that
it was only fitting

01:11:37.918 --> 01:11:40.043
that from Nuremberg, Ben.

01:11:40.044 --> 01:11:43.480
Ferencz, to the Hague,
it was only fitting

01:11:43.481 --> 01:11:44.751
that he would be called

01:11:44.792 --> 01:11:47.146
to do the closing remarks

01:11:47.147 --> 01:11:49.500
of this historic case.

01:11:50.792 --> 01:11:53.459
What makes this
court so distinctive

01:11:54.751 --> 01:11:57.147
is its primary goal to deter

01:11:57.148 --> 01:11:59.542
crimes before they take place

01:11:59.584 --> 01:12:03.542
by letting wrongdoers
know in advance

01:12:03.584 --> 01:12:06.626
that they will be
called to account

01:12:06.667 --> 01:12:08.230
by an impartial

01:12:08.231 --> 01:12:09.792
international criminal court.

01:12:09.834 --> 01:12:11.542
It's not an easy feat to

01:12:11.543 --> 01:12:13.250
create an institution like this.

01:12:13.292 --> 01:12:14.417
It requires courage,

01:12:14.418 --> 01:12:15.542
it requires leadership,

01:12:15.584 --> 01:12:17.751
it requires the right moment

01:12:17.752 --> 01:12:19.918
in historical perspective.

01:12:19.959 --> 01:12:21.500
It requires political will.

01:12:21.542 --> 01:12:23.626
<i>Without Ben, his contribution</i>

01:12:23.627 --> 01:12:25.709
<i>and people like him,</i>

01:12:25.751 --> 01:12:28.059
<i>- this field will not have.
- Evolved the way it already has.</i>

01:12:28.083 --> 01:12:29.667
<i>We still have a long way to go,</i>

01:12:29.709 --> 01:12:31.709
<i>but it's still an
incredible achievement.</i>

01:12:31.751 --> 01:12:32.814
<i>Ben has played a critical</i>

01:12:32.815 --> 01:12:35.751
<i>role in the evolution</i>
of international

01:12:33.918 --> 01:12:35.751
criminal justice

01:12:35.792 --> 01:12:37.167
and in the creation of the ICC.

01:12:37.209 --> 01:12:38.480
Rome Statute for the.

01:12:38.481 --> 01:12:39.751
International Criminal Court

01:12:39.792 --> 01:12:41.084
is one of the strongest

01:12:41.085 --> 01:12:42.375
if not the strongest

01:12:42.417 --> 01:12:44.522
<i>international law treaty</i>

01:12:44.523 --> 01:12:46.626
<i>since the end of World War II.</i>

01:12:46.667 --> 01:12:49.709
<i>You now have an
institution in the Hague</i>

01:12:49.751 --> 01:12:51.251
<i>to hold individuals,</i>

01:12:51.252 --> 01:12:52.751
<i>no matter who they are,</i>

01:12:52.792 --> 01:12:53.834
<i>responsible for committing</i>

01:12:53.835 --> 01:12:54.876
<i>these worst crimes.</i>

01:12:54.918 --> 01:12:57.209
And that's something to continue

01:12:57.210 --> 01:12:59.500
to be very positive about

01:12:59.542 --> 01:13:00.751
and to do everything

01:13:00.752 --> 01:13:01.959
you can to make it work.

01:13:03.125 --> 01:13:05.167
But the job is not done.

01:13:05.209 --> 01:13:09.709
Now we need to persuade
the other states

01:13:09.751 --> 01:13:12.500
to be part of this, this ICC.

01:13:15.500 --> 01:13:16.500
<i>The United States has</i>

01:13:16.501 --> 01:13:18.626
<i>signed the Rome Statute
and the signature</i>

01:13:18.627 --> 01:13:19.709
<i>is still there.</i>

01:13:19.751 --> 01:13:24.542
<i>The problem is,
we are not a ratified party</i>

01:13:24.584 --> 01:13:26.167
<i>to the Rome Statute.</i>

01:13:26.209 --> 01:13:28.292
You know this is part of a

01:13:28.293 --> 01:13:30.375
much larger picture in America.

01:13:30.417 --> 01:13:32.271
We often describe ourselves

01:13:32.272 --> 01:13:34.125
as the exceptional nation.

01:13:34.167 --> 01:13:36.792
<i>We discipline ourselves,</i>

01:13:36.793 --> 01:13:39.417
<i>but we're not eager</i>

01:13:39.459 --> 01:13:41.292
<i>to have any international regime</i>

01:13:41.334 --> 01:13:45.751
<i>with supreme authority
discipline us.</i>

01:13:45.792 --> 01:13:47.376
The attitude is, "Well the."

01:13:47.377 --> 01:13:48.959
United States does this already,

01:13:49.000 --> 01:13:50.626
or the United
States Constitution

01:13:50.667 --> 01:13:51.976
already has these
protections in it.

01:13:52.000 --> 01:13:54.542
<i>Why should we
sacrifice any of that</i>

01:13:54.584 --> 01:13:56.168
<i>to an international</i>

01:13:56.169 --> 01:13:57.751
<i>"regime of any character?"</i>

01:13:57.792 --> 01:14:00.042
<i>Why, because we're the
exceptional nation.</i>

01:14:00.083 --> 01:14:01.667
<i>We will meet all
of these standards,</i>

01:14:01.709 --> 01:14:03.293
but we meet them on our

01:14:03.294 --> 01:14:06.314
terms, not on the terms
being dictated from

01:14:06.315 --> 01:14:07.709
an international body.

01:14:07.751 --> 01:14:09.751
From the outset, the United.

01:14:09.752 --> 01:14:12.959
States was concerned
that maybe it wouldn't

01:14:12.960 --> 01:14:14.125
always be objective.

01:14:14.167 --> 01:14:15.709
That since we were doing

01:14:15.710 --> 01:14:17.250
a lot of the peacekeeping

01:14:17.292 --> 01:14:20.250
and the intervening,
maybe we'd be held

01:14:20.292 --> 01:14:23.000
specifically
specially accountable

01:14:23.042 --> 01:14:28.042
by rival powers who
were on the other side,

01:14:28.876 --> 01:14:31.918
either overtly or covertly.

01:14:31.959 --> 01:14:33.876
And so we couldn't go along.

01:14:33.918 --> 01:14:36.689
U.S. policy makers will say

01:14:36.690 --> 01:14:39.459
it's fine for the Belgians

01:14:39.500 --> 01:14:42.230
and the Brazilians, but we're

01:14:42.231 --> 01:14:44.959
the greatest country on Earth.

01:14:45.000 --> 01:14:50.000
We don't need to be
subject to the same law

01:14:50.042 --> 01:14:51.918
that applies to everyone else.

01:14:51.959 --> 01:14:53.188
And that's true for

01:14:53.189 --> 01:14:54.417
Russia, it's true for China,

01:14:54.459 --> 01:14:56.626
it's true for Pakistan and

01:14:56.627 --> 01:14:58.792
India and Israel and Indonesia.

01:14:58.834 --> 01:15:01.355
And most of the Arab world,

01:15:01.356 --> 01:15:03.876
and we're just not there yet.

01:15:03.918 --> 01:15:07.417
There are 124 countries
that have joined

01:15:07.459 --> 01:15:09.375
the International
Criminal Court.

01:15:09.417 --> 01:15:11.417
That's unfortunate.

01:15:11.459 --> 01:15:14.918
It's a loss in credibility

01:15:14.959 --> 01:15:19.709
in terms of US policy
when these crimes

01:15:19.751 --> 01:15:21.751
arise anywhere in the world.

01:15:24.125 --> 01:15:27.751
<i>No country which
prefers to use its power</i>

01:15:27.792 --> 01:15:29.105
<i>rather than the rule of law</i>

01:15:29.106 --> 01:15:30.417
<i>would vote for the rule of law.</i>

01:15:30.459 --> 01:15:31.751
<i>That's logical.</i>

01:15:31.792 --> 01:15:34.250
<i>That's still the
situation today.</i>

01:15:34.292 --> 01:15:35.938
<i>There are some people who do</i>

01:15:35.939 --> 01:15:37.584
<i>not trust the rule of law,</i>

01:15:37.626 --> 01:15:39.438
<i>and they prefer to use military</i>

01:15:39.439 --> 01:15:41.250
<i>power to achieve their goals</i>

01:15:41.292 --> 01:15:42.563
<i>as they decide and when</i>

01:15:42.564 --> 01:15:43.834
<i>they decide they should.</i>

01:15:43.876 --> 01:15:45.626
That's led by the United States

01:15:45.667 --> 01:15:47.313
to which China replies,

01:15:47.314 --> 01:15:48.959
when you're ready to change

01:15:49.000 --> 01:15:50.500
and give it up, come see me.

01:15:50.542 --> 01:15:51.896
We'll talk about it then

01:15:51.897 --> 01:15:53.250
and the Russians say

01:15:53.292 --> 01:15:54.292
we're not trusting you.

01:15:54.334 --> 01:15:55.417
We don't trust anybody.

01:15:55.459 --> 01:15:57.751
<i>So we have this
political tension</i>

01:15:57.792 --> 01:15:59.542
<i>still exists in the world</i>

01:15:59.584 --> 01:16:00.688
<i>and they're still talking</i>

01:16:00.689 --> 01:16:01.792
<i>about using weaponry</i>

01:16:01.834 --> 01:16:03.563
<i>to settle their disputes,</i>

01:16:03.564 --> 01:16:05.292
<i>not seeming to realize</i>

01:16:05.334 --> 01:16:07.813
<i>how very devastating and</i>

01:16:07.814 --> 01:16:10.292
<i>dangerous that is to themselves</i>

01:16:10.334 --> 01:16:11.876
<i>and to their people.</i>

01:16:14.167 --> 01:16:15.751
<i>It's decisive.</i>

01:16:15.792 --> 01:16:17.834
<i>War will make mass murderers</i>

01:16:17.835 --> 01:16:19.876
<i>out of otherwise decent people</i>

01:16:19.918 --> 01:16:21.418
and I have seen it again

01:16:21.419 --> 01:16:22.918
and again and again.

